 JOHANNESBURG - Seven people were wounded during a shootout in the Johannesburg CBD on Wednesday afternoon. The incident occurred outside a block of flats on Kerk Street in Braamfontein.Paramedics found woman and six men lying outside. "Paramedics immediately assessed the patients and found that two were in a critical condition while the five others had sustained injuries ranging from minor to serious," said ER24 spokesperson Russel Meiring. The patients were transported to various hospitals. The details surrounding the shooting are unclear but police were on the scene to investigate. eNCA